 argues that comparable features and patterns reoccur throughout the corpus, albeit with individual variations contingent on the relevant historical and literary context. A broad range of the literature is considered, including Sagas of Icelanders, Kings' sagas, Contemporary Sagas, Legendary sagas and poems of Christian instruction. HAKI ANTONSSON is Senior Lecturer in Medieval Scandinavian Studies, University College London.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Multiple languages.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aOld Norse literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aSalvation in literature. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAuthority.  aCharismatic Movements.  aCommunity.  aDamnation.  aDeath.  aFamily.  aFear.  aHope.  aLast Things.  aLife-Cycle.  aMaterial World.  aMiddle Ages.  aOld Norse Literature.  aReligious.  aSalvation.  aSpiritual.  aStructure.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311143106240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787443020423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787443020/original  a978-3-11-143106-2  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles